üéØ Objective: Aggregate, correlate, and investigate security events.


üß∞ Core Tools

‚Ä¢ Splunk ‚Äì Log ingestion & query
‚Ä¢ Sigma ‚Äì Rule standardization
‚Ä¢ ATT&CK ‚Äì Mapping tactics/techniques
‚Ä¢ Event Viewer / Sysmon ‚Äì Windows event logging


üß© Step-by-Step Procedure

1Ô∏è‚É£ Logging & Aggregation

‚Ä¢ Ensure sources: Windows, Syslog, EDR, Firewall.

tail -f /var/log/syslog


2Ô∏è‚É£ Correlation (Sigma)

‚Ä¢ Write generic detection logic:

title: Powershell DownloadFile
detection:
  selection:
    EventID: 4688
    CommandLine|contains: "DownloadFile"
  condition: selection


3Ô∏è‚É£ SIEM Query Examples (Splunk)

# Suspicious PowerShell
index=wineventlog EventCode=4688 New_Process_Name="*powershell.exe" CommandLine="*DownloadFile*"

# New local admin creation
index=wineventlog EventCode=4720 OR EventCode=4728 | table _time, user, target_user_name, workstation

# Suspicious Logins
index=windows EventCode=4624 OR EventCode=4625
| stats count by Account_Name, Workstation_Name, IpAddress

# Command Execution
index=sysmon EventCode=1 CommandLine="*powershell*"
| table _time, User, Computer, CommandLine

# Network Anomalies
index=firewall action=allow
| stats count by src_ip, dest_ip, dest_port
| where count > 100



